Rows.descript: new iPad app.

LOC: English, Russian (light txt)

Drilla is the game about drilling the ground to explore the underground world and to study those hidden deep minerals. In the game you can upgrade your digging machine with different parts that can be bought or found in the chests and then crafted from the minerals. There are also upgrades system that will help boosting your digger giving you more speed or mineral amounts. There are also different events that can happen in the mine. For example there is a monster Egor that will disable all the boosters in the mine and girders that are very hard to break but when you do - you’ll get into the new beautiful location.

In this version we added

– Now you can leave the old mine. Go to a new mine — get special acceleration and additives!

– 7 of new mines, each mine now has a level

– Another 15 new parts and skins for your Drilla

– Secret teleport for boost your progress 

– Small fixes

Rows.descript:
New Game // "The award-winning prison escape game now on iOS! While under the careful watch of the guards, players need to go about their daily duties clandestinely secreting useful objects from under their captors’ noses. Escapees will learn how to craft seemingly innocuous items into useful tools and weapons as well as using them to execute cunning diversionary tactics. 

Players will need to learn when to keep in line, utilising their time sensibly as they develop their own personal plans of escape. Learning the prison’s daily routines and spotting opportunities are all part of life behind bars. 
Whilst remembering to attend roll-call, holding down their job and keeping their fellow inmates on side, players can also benefit from advancing their character's statistics through various means including boosting their intellect and exercising regularly. Balance mundane routine with careful planning to attain your ultimate goal - escape and freedom!
"
Rows.comments: This is an adventure game where your goal is to escape from prison, each prison having its own ways of getting out. Item crafting, character interactions, it will take puzzle solving to get out of each prison. The game uses a weird hybrid of pixel art and smooth text that makes everything feel slapped together. The controls are VERY clunky as they tried to shoehorn touch-screen interactions with virtual analog/buttons so your hand are constantly swapping around. Text windows plaster on top of the action frequently, too.
